Harvard researchers looked 
at nine perspective studies

11:06.899 --> 11:09.668
finding that just one serving 
of processed meat per day

11:09.668 --> 11:13.839
increased risk of 
developing diabetes by 51%.

11:13.839 --> 11:15.074
The link between eating meat

11:15.074 --> 11:17.977
and developing diabetes 
became undeniable.

11:17.977 --> 11:19.178
But when I went on

11:19.178 --> 11:20.946
the leading diabetes 
organization's website,

11:20.946 --> 11:22.915
the American 
Diabetes Association,

11:22.915 --> 11:24.583
not only did they not 
have this information

11:24.583 --> 11:27.386
front and center, they 
were featuring recipes

11:27.386 --> 11:30.056
for red and processed 
meat and on there,

11:30.056 --> 11:31.991
Recipes for Healthy Living.

11:31.991 --> 11:34.193
They had bacon wrapped shrimp?

11:34.193 --> 11:36.328
What the health?

